  "elapsed_s": 4.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And-- and less than a year ago, our younger daughter and her husband and their baby came to Israel with us.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So we-- we-- we make our lives an integral part of their lives, and our lives were defined early on by the Holocaust, and the last 50 years in the value of a free and open society and the prevention of any future nightmares.",
      "word_count": 44
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, Annette is a Holocaust survivor in a different way.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "She received protection from the Portuguese minister to Hungary, who received his inspiration from Wallenberg.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And she left with the Portuguese minister, Mr.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "[INAUDIBLE], during the most difficult period of 1944 for Switzerland.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So in a sense, Raoul Wallenberg saved my life directly and Raoul Wallenberg saved Annette's life indirectly.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I need to tell you that when the Holocaust Museum opened and there was a special children's program, one of our granddaughters, Chelsea, played what to me was an unbelievably moving role in that children's program.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "She wrote a letter to Raoul Wallenberg, thanking him for saving the lives of her grandfather and grandmother so her mother could be born and so that she could be born.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And when we placed Raoul Wallenberg-- Wallenberg's statue in the Capital, there were five speakers-- the speaker of our Congress, the speaker of the Israeli Knesset, the speaker of the Hungarian Parliament, the speaker of the Swedish Parliament, and our granddaughter, Chelsea.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So it was very difficult for us not to-- not to cry very hard because it was an incredibly moving moment.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "It was on national television, and we all felt that this 12-year-old girl captured the essence of what Raoul Wallenberg was probably better than the many books that have been written about him.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It's very simple, [?",
      "word_count": 4
    }
  ],
